<HEADLINE>
<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: LOS ANGELES; ALL 
ELECTED CITY OFFICIALS WILL WAIVE 5% PAY RAISE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 All 18 elected officials in the city of Los Angeles declared before a Tuesday 
deadline that they will waive a 5% pay increase scheduled to begin in the New 
Year, or else donate the money to charity or other causes. 
</P>
<P>
 Thirteen City Council members joined Mayor Richard Riordan, City Atty.James K. 
Hahn and City Controller Rick Tuttle in waiving the raises. Council members 
would have received hikes from $90,680 to $95,214. 
</P>
<P>
 Council members Hal Bernson and Nate Holden said they will give their raises 
to aid the community. Bernson said his will go to the Devonshire and Foothill 
police divisions; Holden will give his to the American Youth Foundation. 
</P>
<P>
 Council members said that during a time of economic hardship they were 
uncomfortable taking the raises -- which were tied to those of Municipal Court 
judges by a 1990 law. The city will save nearly $70,000 because of the waivers. 
</P>
