<HEADLINE>
<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: VAN NUYS; MENENDEZ 
JURIES SPEND QUIET DAY IN DELIBERATION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The two juries in the Menendez brothers' murder trial deliberated quietly 
Tuesday, sending no notes to the judge and putting in a full day's work behind 
closed doors. 
</P>
<P>
 Lyle Menendez's jury wrapped up a 14th day of deliberations. Erik Menendez's 
jury finished a 12th day. 
</P>
<P>
 Two juries are deciding the case against Lyle Menendez, 25, and Erik Menendez, 
23, because some evidence was admissible against only one brother. 
</P>
<P>
 Both are charged with murder in the Aug. 20, 1989, shotgun slayings of their 
parents, entertainment executive Jose Menendez, 45, and Kitty Menendez, 47. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Brief 
</P>
</TYPE>
