<P>
 The Ventura County coroner's office Tuesday identified two men who burned to 
death when their car flipped over and burst into flames on California 126 near 
Fillmore over the weekend. 
</P>
<P>
 The victims were identified as Efraim Ramirez, 53, the driver of the car, and 
Ezequiel Nunez, 65, a passenger, Deputy Coroner Jim Wingate said.Both men were 
farm laborers from Fillmore and are survived by wives and other family members 
in Mexico, he said. The men were identified using X-rays and dental records. 
</P>
