<HEADLINE>
<P>
COUNTYWIDE FOCUS: WOMAN SEXUALLY ASSAULTED AT BEACH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SCOTT HADLY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 22-year-old Thousand Oaks woman was sexually assaulted and robbed at 
knifepoint in a midday attack at a Ventura County beach, authorities said 
Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
 The woman was sunbathing at La Conchita Beach along the Ventura Freeway at 
noon Monday when she was approached by a man.He first tried to engage the woman 
in conversation and then left the area, said Sgt. John Fitzgerald of the 
Ventura County Sheriff's Department major crimes unit. 
</P>
<P>
 Although there were other sunbathers on the beach, no one noticed when the man 
returned an hour later with a knife and forced the woman to move into a 
drainage tunnel at the edge of the beach, Fitzgerald said. The man forced her 
to disrobe and then sexually assaulted her, Fitzgerald said. 
</P>
<P>
 The assailant stole the woman's money and credit cards, then told her to count 
to 100 before she left the tunnel or he would kill her, the Sheriff's 
Department reported. 
</P>
<P>
 The woman was treated at Ventura County Medical Center and released, 
Fitzgerald said. 
</P>
<P>
 The Sheriff's Department described the suspect as a white male 36 to 40 years 
old, with short brown hair and a thick mustache. He was wearing a white T-shirt 
and baggy blue jeans. The department is encouraging anyone with information to 
contact the major crimes unit at 654-2331 or 654-2311. SCOTT HADLY 
</P>
</TEXT>
