<P>
COUNTYWIDE FOCUS: HOWARD TO CHAIR BOARD OF SUPERVISORS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By TINA DAUNT 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 In a change of command for the new year, Ventura County Supervisor Vicky 
Howard on Tuesday was named chairwoman of the board for 1994. 
</P>
<P>
 Howard, who served as the board's assistant chairwoman last year, will replace 
Susan K. Lacey in the leadership position. 
</P>
<P>
 Every January, the supervisors rotate one of their colleagues into the slot. 
Howard will be responsible for making sure that the meetings are conducted in 
an orderly fashion. 
</P>
<P>
 "I think I will enjoy it," said Howard, who has served on the board since 
1990. "I always enjoy challenges." 
</P>
<P>
 Meanwhile, Supervisor Maria E. VanderKolk was named assistant chairwoman and 
will fill in for Howard when she is absent. 
</P>
<P>
 "I hope you're sick at least once," VanderKolk laughingly told Howard. TINA 
DAUNT 
</P>
