<HEADLINE>
<P>
FISHING REPORT: NIGHTCRAWLERS STILL BEST WHEN ANGLING FOR BASS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Plastic worms have nothing on the real thing. Nightcrawlers remain the top 
bass-catchers and bass fishermen have been doing plenty of catching during the 
past week at the Los Angeles County reservoir. 
</P>
<P>
 Steve and Phil Arklin of Sand Canyon, with guide Bob Crupi, used the 
earthworms to catch several bass, the largest a 15-pounder; Chris Poffenberger 
of Sylmar used a worm to entice a 14-pound 8-ounce bass; Randy Leech of Castaic 
used one to land a 13-4 largemouth, and Ron Kubes Jr. of Castaic used one to 
hook a 9-9 bass. 
</P>
<P>
 Several smaller bass were taken on plastic worms and other lures. 
</P>
