<HEADLINE>
<P>
SANTA ANA VALLEY ROLLS PAST NO. 10 MAGNOLIA, 68-28 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MICHAEL ITAGAKI 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The showdown between two of Orange County's best teams turned into a blowout 
Tuesday as third-ranked Santa Ana Valley forced 27 turnovers and posted a 68-28 
victory over 10th-ranked Magnolia in a nonleague boys' basketball game at Santa 
Ana Valley. 
</P>
<P>
 Magnolia shot 22% (11 of 51) from the field against a tenacious Santa Ana 
Valley defense.The Falcons (14-2) held Magnolia to 10 points in the second and 
third quarters combined to take a 53-20 lead into the fourth quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 Frank Henderson, the Sentinels' top scorer who is averaging 17 points, missed 
all seven shots he took and did not play in the second half. Magnolia also 
played without starting center Brandon Hearvey. 
</P>
<P>
 "We didn't expect a 40-point game tonight," Santa Ana Valley Coach Rich 
Prospero said. "It was a little ragged, but I accept that from this team. When 
you press and want to play up-tempo with a young point guard, that's how it 
gets." 
</P>
<P>
 Sophomore point guard Olujimi Mann finished with 11 points, seven rebounds, 
four assists, four steals and five turnovers. Mann and most of the starters did 
not play in the fourth quarter for Santa Ana Valley. 
</P>
<P>
 Michael Riggins scored a team-high 13 points and Darnell Adamson added 10 
points and nine rebounds for the Falcons, who had 11 players score. 
</P>
<P>
 La Shawn Neal had eight points and Todd Callahan had 11 rebounds for Magnolia 
(10-5). MICHAEL ITAGAKI 
</P>
