<P>
PREP ROUNDUP; MARINA'S UNBEATEN STREAK IN SOCCER AT 24 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MARTIN BECK 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Marina, the top-ranked girls' soccer team in Orange County and the Southern 
Section Division I, took a step toward proving it is the best team in the 
Sunset League by defeating Ocean View, 3-0, Tuesday at Ocean View. 
</P>
<P>
 Ocean View (9-5-1, 0-1 in league), ranked fifth in Orange County, made a game 
of it early, but Marina (14-0, 1-0) had too many weapons and extended its 
unbeaten streak to 24 games. 
</P>
<P>
 Last season, the Vikings finished their league season with five victories 
after losing a second league game -- to Edison. 
</P>
<P>
 "This year we don't want to lose a game in league," Marina Coach Bobby Bruch 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 Seven minutes into the game Tuesday, midfielder Cassie Campbell gave the 
Vikings the lead with a goal off a rebound of her own shot. It was Campbell's 
17th goal of the season. 
</P>
<P>
 A minute later, Ocean View nearly tied the score when Marina goalkeeper 
Jennifer Simmons slipped in the mud near the goal, leaving an open net, but the 
Seahawks were not able to get a shot on goal. Simmons made a nice save of a 
header by Shannon Donegan with about 12 minutes left in the half. Then with 
five minutes left, Simmons slipped again but Marina defenders were able to 
protect the open net. 
</P>
<P>
 Marina scored twice in the first 21 minutes of the second half. Jenny Benson 
made a crossing pass that somehow found the corner of the goal and Rhiannon 
Tanaka beat Ocean View goalkeeper Lynn Brown to the ball near the endline and 
made a perfect crossing pass to Megan Orach in front of an empty goal. MARTIN 
BECK 
</P>
