BANK WORKERS ARRESTED IN IRAN OVER FORGED ACCOUNTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Police have arrested a group of Iranian bank employees suspected of siphoning 
off $3.6 million from government accounts, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 Gen. Reza Seifollahi, in remarks published in Kayhan newspaper Tuesday, said 
all the money was recovered from the group, which forged accounts in the 
state-owned Melli Bank. 
