<HEADLINE>
<P>
BROWN SETS UP EDUCATION HOT LINE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 In preparation for a statewide education summit next month, Assembly Speaker 
Willie Brown has set up a 24-hour toll-free hot line to accept suggestions on 
how to improve California's public schools. 
</P>
<P>
 Those suggestions will be considered by legislators and educators at the 
summit, to be held on Feb. 15 and 16 at the Westin St. Francis Hotel in San 
Francisco. 
</P>
<P>
 The hot line number is 1-800-773-2594 (1-800-SPEAK-94). Tapes of phoned-in 
suggestions might be played at the summit, Brown said. 
</P>
<P>
 The education summit is aimed at analyzing the condition of California's 
public education system and devising solutions to its problems. In preparation 
for the two-day forum, local summits will be held around the state this month, 
allowing Assembly members, parents, teachers and school board members to focus 
on local issues. 
</P>
</TEXT>
