<HEADLINE>
<P>
ATHLETE OF THE WEEK: GIRLS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Shawanda Hotchkiss 
</P>
<P>
 SCHOOL: Channel Islands 
</P>
<P>
 SPORT: Basketball 
</P>
<P>
 YEAR: Senior 
</P>
<P>
 SEASON AT A GLANCE: Hotchkiss has been the catalyst for a talented Raider 
squad that won 10 of its first 12 games. The 5-foot-7 guard was named to the 
all-tournament team in the Alemany and Gold Coast tournaments, and she leads 
the Raiders in scoring (14 points a game), steals (2.1) and field-goal 
percentage (49%). 
</P>
<P>
 WEEK AT A GLANCE: Hotchkiss was named most valuable player of last week's 
Thousand Oaks tournament, won by Channel Islands. She averaged 15 points in the 
four victories, and had 16 points and eight rebounds in the championship game 
against Thousand Oaks. "She's doing a lot better than last year," Coach Don 
Salado said. "Her all-around play and her attitude have really improved." 
</P>
