<HEADLINE>
<P>
ATHLETE OF THE WEEK: BOYS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Eric Spindt 
</P>
<P>
 SCHOOL: Hart 
</P>
<P>
 SPORT: Basketball 
</P>
<P>
 YEAR: Senior 
</P>
<P>
 SEASON AT A GLANCE: Spindt, a two-year varsity starter, is a steadying force 
for the Indians (15-1), who are ranked first in The Times' regional poll. A 
skilled ballhandler who rarely makes bad decisions, Spindt has team-leading 
averages of 5.7 assists and 2.1 steals.He also averages 10.6 points and 4.5 
rebounds for the three-time defending Foothill League champions. 
</P>
<P>
 WEEK AT A GLANCE: Spindt was named most valuable player of the 22nd Hart 
tournament after scoring 18 points and dealing out five assists in the 
championship game, a 67-55 victory over City Section power Manual Arts. Spindt, 
who was also named MVP of the Beverly Hills tournament, made nine of 10 free 
throws in the fourth quarter. Spindt averaged 10.5 points and 5.8 assists in 
Hart's four games during the tournament. "I didn't put up super numbers every 
game, but I got the job done," Spindt said. 
</P>
