<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE BASKETBALL ROUNDUP; CAL LUTHERAN ROLLS TO 10TH IN ROW, 131-59 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Cal Lutheran men's basketball team rolled over California Christian, 
131-59, on Tuesday night in Fresno, extending the team's school-record start to 
10-0. 
</P>
<P>
 Damon Ridley led the Kingsmen with 21 points and seven assists. 
</P>
<P>
 Paul Tapp came off the bench to score 20 points for Cal Lutheran. Derrick 
Clark (19 points), Rob Beckerly (16), Paul LaMott (14) and Kenny Caesar (11) 
also scored in double figures for the Kingsmen. 
</P>
<P>
 Joey Salazar led the Contenders (2-7) with 12 points. 
</P>
<P>
 Cal Lutheran shot 59% from the field, compared with California Christian's 
30%. WOMEN 
</P>
<P>
 Glendale 56, Cuesta 53 -- Susie Woo made three three-pointers and scored 13 
points to lead the Vaqueros (5-6) in a Western State Conference opener at 
Glendale. 
</P>
<P>
 Makela Theriault (12 points) and Keri Peterson (11) also scored in double 
figures for Glendale. The Vaqueros won despite making only one of 15 free 
throws in the second half. 
</P>
<P>
 Michelle Cornell led Cuesta (5-6) with 22 points. 
</P>
<P>
 Ventura 73, Pierce 30 -- Camisca Hawkins scored 17 points and Amy Blackburn 
added 16 points and 13 rebounds for Ventura (11-4) in a Western State 
Conference inter-division opener at Pierce. 
</P>
<P>
 Moorpark 57, Bakersfield 44 -- Janette Oriza had 13 points and 13 rebounds for 
the Raiders (4-10) in a Western State Conference opener at Bakersfield. 
</P>
<P>
 Lisa Church also had 13 points for Moorpark. 
</P>
<P>
 Southern California College 65, The Master's College 33 -- Tina Demarsh scored 
18 points and Southern California College held The Master's to 12 first-half 
points in a nonconference game at Newhall. 
</P>
<P>
 Sharlene TeVelde led The Master's (2-6) with 11 points and six rebounds. 
</P>
