<HEADLINE>
<P>
HIGH SCHOOL ROUNDUP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 No. 1 Hart Survives Scare, 61-43 
</P>
<P>
 Burroughs High came into Hart's gym with a 1-9 record but was able to give the 
top-ranked Indians something of a scare. 
</P>
<P>
 Burroughs held a one-point lead at halftime and led by as many as seven in the 
third quarter of the Foothill League game Tuesday night before falling, 61-43. 
</P>
<P>
 Hart's stifling man-to-man defense and sharp passing finally took over in the 
fourth quarter when Hart (15-1) outscored Burroughs, 28-15. 
</P>
<P>
 Eric Spindt had 17 points for Hart, which posted its 12th consecutive victory. 
Jess Rowland scored 12 for Burroughs. 
</P>
<P>
 In other boys' basketball games: 
</P>
<P>
 Crenshaw 121, Hoover 50 -- Tremaine Fowlkes and Kristaan Johnson combined for 
58 points to lead host Crenshaw in a nonleague game. Andreh Allaharyn scored 19 
for Hoover (7-7). 
</P>
<P>
 Highland 61, Quartz Hill 43 -- Highland (8-4, 3-1) won a Golden League game 
behind 23 points and 12 rebounds by Pharoah Davis. 
</P>
<P>
 Santa Clara 61, Carpinteria 44 -- The Saints (7-7) outscored Carpinteria, 
20-6, in the fourth quarter of the nonleague game. Damian Cantrell had 27 
points and 10 steals. Kevin Collins had 12 rebounds and seven points. 
</P>
<P>
 Glendale 56, Dana Hills 36 -- Ramon Jose scored 20 points and had six of the 
Dynamiters' 13 steals to lead Glendale (12-4) past Dana Hills (7-8) in a 
nonleague game. 
</P>
<P>
 Saugus 47, Burbank 42 -- Ryan Berg had 13 points and nine rebounds to lead 
Saugus (9-6, 2-1) to a Foothill League victory at Burbank. Isaiah Kearson 
scored 15 points on five three-pointers and Brad Warner had 12 on four 
three-pointers for Burbank (5-8, 0-3). 
</P>
<P>
 L.A. Baptist 70, St. Genevieve 42 -- Matt Beck and Ryan O'Connell each scored 
11 points for the Knights (9-3) in a nonleague game. 
</P>
<P>
 Crescenta Valley 72, Schurr 60 -- Brock Jacobsen scored 24 points to lead the 
Falcons' rout in a nonleague game at Crescenta Valley. 
</P>
<P>
 Richard O'Neill scored 17 for the Falcons (10-4) and Blake Jacobson had 14 
points and 13 rebounds. 
</P>
<P>
 Verdugo Hills 78, Wilson 72 -- Chan Cornish had 26 points and 18 rebounds to 
lead the Dons (4-5, 2-1) to a Northern Conference victory. Dave Bryant added 17 
points and seven assists. 
</P>
<P>
 Antelope Valley 61, Littlerock 55 -- The Antelopes made 23 of 26 free throws 
in a Golden League game. Freddy Gonzales scored 15 points. John George had 30 
points and 13 rebounds for Littlerock. GIRLS' BASKETBALL 
</P>
