<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE ROUNDUP; CHAPMAN USES TWO BIG RUNS TO TOP CLAREMONT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By TOM BIRSCHBACH 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Chapman had little difficulty building a big lead early against Claremont 
College on Tuesday night but holding on to it proved to be much tougher. 
</P>
<P>
 The Panthers finally emerged with an 83-74 victory in Orange to run their 
record to 7-4. 
</P>
<P>
 Chapman took a 15-2 lead on Greg Reynolds' three-point basket with 14:52 left 
in the first half and cruised to a 38-31 halftime lead. In the second half, 
Claremont made a 23-7 run and led 54-44 with 14:29 left in the game as Stag 
forward Chris Fosse scored eight consecutive points. 
</P>
<P>
 "We went from seven up to 10 down quicker than any team I've ever been 
associated with," said Panther Coach Mike Bokosky. "They're strong inside. 
They're good players." 
</P>
<P>
 With Claremont (3-5) leading 58-57 on Fosse's basket with 9:05 remaining, the 
Panthers went on a 14-3 run for a 71-61 lead with 5:53 left. A pair of 
three-point baskets by Anthony Gonzales and a three-point play by Umahl 
Anderson highlighted the run. Chapman's free-throw shooting down the stretch 
preserved the lead. 
</P>
<P>
 Stefan Mumaw and Anderson led Chapman with 16 and 14 points. Fosse and former 
Laguna Beach standout Darren Gravley led Claremont with 20 and 18 points. TOM 
BIRSCHBACH 
</P>
</TEXT>
