<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY COLLEGE ATHLETES OF THE WEEK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Antoine Jefferson 
</P>
<P>
 Saddleback, So. 
</P>
<P>
 Basketball / Forward 
</P>
<P>
 Jefferson doesn't need a full game to show off his offensive skills.He scored 
51 points in three games and was the most valuable player as Saddleback won the 
Rancho Santiago Holiday tournament. Of his points total, 41 came in the second 
half of the three games. He didn't score in the first half until the title 
game, an 89-68 victory over Long Beach. Jefferson, from Philadelphia, is 
averaging 16 points and nine rebounds for Saddleback, which opens Orange Empire 
Conference play tonight at 7 at Fullerton. Other notables: 
</P>
<P>
 * Derrick Walsh scored 23 points for Saddleback in an 89-68 victory over Long 
Beach in the final of the Rancho Santiago Holiday tournament. 
</P>
