<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY COLLEGE ATHLETES OF THE WEEK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Christy Kahlbenn 
</P>
<P>
 Cypress, So. 
</P>
<P>
 Basketball / Guard 
</P>
<P>
 Kahlbenn, from Rancho Alamitos High, last played basketball in 1989-90 for 
Christ College Irvine.She has quickly returned to form for Cypress this season. 
Kahlbenn had her best performance in the Fullerton tournament, scoring 26 
points, including five three-pointers, and had 12 rebounds to help Cypress beat 
Fullerton, 66-57, in the third-place game. She scored 23 points in the first 
half, including four three-pointers, as the Chargers opened a 40-26 lead. She 
averaged 12 points and six rebounds for the four games. Other notables: 
</P>
<P>
 * LeAnn Kazmer of Orange Coast scored 46 points and had 28 rebounds as Orange 
Coast lost twice in the San Jose tournament. 
