<HEADLINE>
<P>
EAST VALLEY FOCUS: VAN NUYS; MAN GETS JAIL FOR TAGGING POLICE CAR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By THOM MROZEK 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A reputed gang member from Reseda has been sentenced to seven months in County 
Jail for spray-painting a police car with the penal code number for murder. 
</P>
<P>
 Jose Antonio Guzman, 22, was convicted Dec. 23 on misdemeanor charges of 
vandalism and vehicle tampering for painting the black and white police unit 
and slashing its tires. 
</P>
<P>
 The Los Angeles police car was sprayed with "187," the number of the the 
California Penal Code section for murder. Prosecutors said this message is used 
by gangs as a warning that someone has been targeted for murder. 
</P>
<P>
 During a short hearing Monday in Van Nuys Municipal Court, Judge Paul I. 
Metzler sentenced Guzman to 213 days in jail -- six months for the offense and 
another 33 days because Guzman said he would spend time in custody rather than 
pay a $1,000 fine. 
</P>
<P>
 Metzler said that Guzman failed to show any remorse for his actions and that 
he lied during his trial when he testified he did not confess to the vandalism. 
</P>
<P>
 The sentence was the maximum allowed by law. 
</P>
<P>
 Authorities said Guzman and a 15-year-old juvenile, who also has been 
convicted, vandalized the police car when officers responded to a loud house 
party in Winnetka on Aug. 21. THOM MROZEK 
</P>
</TEXT>
