<HEADLINE>
<P>
EAST VALLEY FOCUS: SHERMAN OAKS; NANCY SCHMIDT TO LEAD CHAMBER IN '94 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SCOTT GLOVER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A Sherman Oaks bank vice president who is a veteran San Fernando Valley 
business leader has been elected president of the Sherman Oaks Chamber of 
Commerce. 
</P>
<P>
 Nancy Schmidt will take over from outgoing chamber President Jeff Brain, who 
did not seek reelection, Jan. 18. 
</P>
<P>
 Schmidt, president of the San Fernando Valley Charitable Foundation and a 
member of the North Hollywood Rotary Club and Valley Industry and Commerce 
Assn., said she will use those connections to build chamber membership. 
</P>
<P>
 "The more organizations you know and belong to, the better you can help the 
whole group network," Schmidt said. "That's what I am going to try to do." 
</P>
<P>
 Schmidt also anticipates playing the role of cheerleader to businesses 
rebounding from the recession by launching a marketing campaign to revitalize 
business and through a series of luncheon speeches. 
</P>
<P>
 "She'll be good for the chamber," Brain said of the president-elect. "And 
she's going to have lots of good people around her." 
</P>
<P>
 The 1994 officers and board of directors will be installed at the chamber's 
annual recognition and installation dinner at the Sportsmen's Lodge in Studio 
City. 
</P>
<P>
 Others elected to the chamber's executive board were Brain, Barry Wegman, 
Kathleen Holland, Scott Sandefur, Scott Tripp, Ron Mitnick, Carrie Konjoyan and 
Judy Davis. SCOTT GLOVER 
</P>
</TEXT>
