<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY: COMPANY TOWN ANNEX 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Kanter Leaves MGM: Longtime Hollywood figure Jay Kanter has resigned as 
chairman of production at Metro-Goldwyn-Mayer.Kanter's leaving had been 
expected after the departure in July of Alan Ladd Jr., his longtime associate. 
Kanter worked at MGM or related companies since 1984. The studio, owned by 
French bank Credit Lyonnais, is now trying to rebuild under a new executive 
team led by former Paramount Pictures Chairman Frank Mancuso. 
</P>
</TEXT>
