BRIEFLY: ENERGY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Mobil to Take Large 4th-Quarter Charge: Mobil Corp. said it will take a 
non-cash charge of $250 million to earnings because of "the recent dramatic 
decline in worldwide crude oil prices." In a news release, the company said the 
charge covers excess of inventory book value over current market values, 
reflecting the decline in crude and product prices since 1982, when Mobil 
adopted last in/first out accounting in its international marketing and 
refining operations. 
</P>
