<P>
 Source: Morgan Stanley Capital International MEXICAN STOCKS 
</P>
<P>
 * After plummeting 100.4 points Monday on news of peasant riots near the 
southern border, the Bolsa index rebounded 56.66 points Tuesday to close at 
2,558.89. Earlier in the day, sellers had pushed the Bolsa down more than 38 
points in a continuation of Monday's decline. 
</P>
<P>
 * While analysts say the peasant revolt doesn't threaten the stability of the 
government of President Carlos Salinas de Gortari, it points up the unevenness 
of the spread of wealth in Mexico under Salinas' economic reforms. But few 
analysts believe the official path of reform will change -- thus, international 
investors aren't expected to walk away from Mexican stocks for long. 
</P>
