BRIEFCASE: REAL ESTATE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by John O'Dell, Times staff writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 What Does It Mean? Deciphering what the permit and sales increases mean, and 
predicting where things are going this year, will be the topic of the Orange 
County Building Industry Assn.'s inaugural meeting for 1994. 
</P>
<P>
 The Jan. 17 dinner at the Irvine Marriott will feature economists Dennis 
Aigner, dean of the graduate school of management at UC Irvine; and James Doti, 
president of the private Chapman University in Orange and former director of 
its Center for Economic Research. 
</P>
<P>
 Both universities turn out annual forecasts of the county economy, and Aigner 
and Doti have been asked to share their thinking about what the future holds 
for the housing industry specifically. 
</P>
