<P>
ORANGE COUNTY BRIEFLY: HELIONETICS OKS ASSETS DEAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Irvine's Helionetics Inc. said Tuesday that it has reached an agreement to 
purchase assets and assume liabilities of New York-based Kerby Saunders-Warkol 
Inc., doing business as JWP Mechanical Services, a subsidiary of JWP Inc. 
Financial terms of the transaction were not disclosed. JWP Mechanical Services 
maintains and repairs high-technology and energy-saving products. Helionetics 
makes power equipment and computer products for the health-care and defense 
industries. 
</P>
