ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: COUNTYWIDE; SUPERIOR COURT JUDGE IS SWORN IN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 H. Warren Siegel was sworn in as judge of the Orange County Superior Court 
last week. 
</P>
<P>
 Appointed by Gov. Pete Wilson in November, Siegel, 54, fills the vacancy 
created by the retirement of Robert C. Todd. 
</P>
<P>
 Siegel formerly practiced with an Irvine law firm focusing primarily on 
business litigation and labor issues. He also served as deputy attorney general 
for California from 1963 to 1971. 
</P>
<P>
 Siegel received his undergraduate degree from UCLA and a law degree from the 
University of Chicago. 
