ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: FOUNTAIN VALLEY; VOLUNTEERS SOUGHT FOR CITY PANELS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Volunteers are needed to serve on various city committees and commissions. 
</P>
<P>
 The deadline to apply is today and applications are available in the city 
clerk's office, 10200 Slater Ave.Deadline to submit applications is 5 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
 Seats on the following are open:  
</P>
<P>
 * Planning Commission; makes recommendations to the City Council regarding 
such issues as development, subdivision of land, the city's Master Plan, 
blighted and substandard areas, and zoning and land use. 
</P>
<P>
 * Community Services Commission; formulates policies on recreation services. 
</P>
<P>
 * Traffic Committee; assists in the preparation and publication of traffic 
reports, receives complaints regarding traffic issues and makes recommendations 
to improve traffic. 
</P>
<P>
 * Housing and Community Development Advisory Board; reviews the city's block 
grant program and other housing issues. 
</P>
<P>
 * Advisory Committee for the Disabled; oversees the development of facilities 
for people with disabilities and oversees recreational, informational and 
educational programs for people with disabilities. 
</P>
<P>
 * Fountain Valley Improvement Authority; responsible for the approval of the 
annual audit of financial activities. 
</P>
<P>
 * Alcohol and Drug Awareness Committee; addresses drug-related issues in the 
areas of education, intervention and enforcement efforts. 
</P>
<P>
 * Environmental Education Team; serves to educate public understanding of 
waste management issues. 
</P>
<P>
 More information is available by calling the city clerk at (714) 965-4400. 
</P>
